The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                        
	Manesar: The Athletics Federation of India (AFI) Sunday suspended as many as 15 of its units for not holding state meets and not following the AFI calendar. Also, seeking to make track and field dope free, the AFI decided to prepare its own whereabouts information and collect samples from suspected athletes anytime and from anywhere in the country.        
	Valencia: Spanish long-distance runner Sergio Sanchez has broken the European indoor 3,000m record. Sanchez ran a time of 7 minutes, 32.41 seconds at Valencias Luis Puig Stadium on Saturday, beating the 7:32.98 mark set by Spanish compatriot Alberto Garcia in 2003.      
	Ashwin wins  
	Chennai: Ashwin Sundar, driving for Narain Karthikeyans Speed Team, weathered the challenge of three experienced drivers to clinch the Overall Championship title in Formula 1600CC three-legged (six races) MRF Challenge series here Sunday.      
	Kannur: Chirag United overcame Pune FC 2-1 in their Pool B league encounter of the 3rd EK Nayanar Memorial Gold Cup Football tournament here on Sunday. Edmilson and Joshimar scored for Chirag while Muthumani was on the mark for Pune FC.        
	Calcutta: The CFL premier division match between Mohammedan Sporting and Railway FC, which was scheduled to be held on Monday, has been postponed and will now take place on Tuesday, at the Salt Lake stadium.        
	Calcutta: Australian Rodney Tucker will make his international Test match umpiring debut on Monday when he officiates in the first Test between New Zealand and Bangladesh at Seddon Park in Hamilton. The 45-year-old former first-class player for New South Wales and Tasmania took up umpiring after his playing career finished and has since quickly moved his way up the umpiring ranks.        
	Calcutta: Former Australian opener William Bill Lawry and pace bowler Graham Garth McKenzie will be officially inducted into the Australian Cricket Hall of Fame at the 2010 Allan Border Medal on Monday.        
	Karachi: Former Pakistan captain Aamir Sohail has called for an early resumption of cricketing ties with India to repair the damaged relations between the two countries after the 2008 Mumbai terror attacks. Lets get Pakistan-India games back It brings both nations together, builds bridges and makes friends, Sohail said.                                                                                                                                                      
